## Why This Is Asked

This question probes practical multi-tenant isolation, policy-as-code, and operational testing in GCP.

## Key Concepts

- Shared VPC and host projects
- IAM Conditions for per-tenant access
- VPC Service Controls for data exfil prevention
- Billing Budgets and cost monitoring per tenant
- Cloud Asset Inventory for drift detection
- CI/CD with Terraform and Cloud Build
- Policy-as-code (OPA) and guardrails

## Code Example

```javascript
// sample budget per tenant
resource "google_billing_budget" "tenant_budget" {
  billing_account = var.billing_account_id
  display_name    = "tenant-${var.tenant_id}-budget"

  amount {
    specified_amount {
      currency_code = "USD"
      units         = 1000
    }
  }

  threshold_rules {
    threshold_percent = 0.8
    spend_basis       = "CURRENT_SPEND"
  }

  // optional fields omitted for brevity
}
```

```javascript
// per-tenant IAM condition (example)
resource "google_project_iam_member" "tenant_view" {
  project = var.tenant_project_id
  role    = "roles/viewer"
  member  = "user:${var.user_email}"
  condition {
    title       = "tenant_is_owner"
    expression  = "resource.name.startsWith('projects/${var.tenant_project_id}')"
  }
}
```

