## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of secret rotation, zero-downtime deployments, and basic auditing in GCP.

## Key Concepts

- Secret Manager secret versioning and rotation
- Cloud SQL user credential management
- Rolling updates in Cloud Run
- IAM least privilege and Audit Logs
- Cloud Scheduler and Cloud Functions

## Code Example

```javascript
// Example Cloud Function to rotate secret
const {SecretManagerServiceClient} = require('@google-cloud/secret-manager');
const client = new SecretManagerServiceClient();
async function rotateSecret(name, value){
  const [version] = await client.addSecretVersion({ parent: name, payload: { data: Buffer.from(value) } });
  return version;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test this rotation flow locally? 
- How would you implement a rollback if the new secret fails to be used by Cloud Run?

## Why This Is Asked
Assesses how a candidate combines deployment strategies, DR planning, and enforcement of security/compliance in a real GCP setup.

## Key Concepts
- Blue/Green and canary deployments with automatic rollback gates
- Cross-region DR for compute and database
- CMEK encryption for storage and Cloud SQL
- Policy-as-code and drift detection (Config Connector, OPA)
- Observability, outage handling, and compliance

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudo-code for SLO gate
async function canaryGate(metrics) {
  const latencyOk = metrics.p95 < 200;
  const errorOk = metrics.errorRate < 0.01;
  return latencyOk && errorOk;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you validate drift detection in CI/CD and ensure fast remediations?
- What tests would you run to validate cross-region failover without customer-visible downtime?

